Introduction

The tables below have been generated from programmatic data to facilitate SCP 2020 reporting. Where additional information is required, please get in touch with the HIS team on the email address above.

To assist in extraction of aggregated information presented in this report, two buttons have been added to each table. To copy the table for pasting in other documents, press COPY. To download the table as a csv file, press CSV.

A brief explanation of each table is provided in the relevent section. Data has not been checked during this analysis, so results are raw and simply reflect what is entered into project databases.

Admissions

Admission data is taken from the registration form and aggregated by year and month. Any patient who is admitted on different days will be recorded twice, for example, a patient who is admitted, discharged, then re-admitted at a later date.

Consultations

Follow up visits have been combined with diabetic annual review visits to calculate the number of consultations performed in any given month. Multiple visits by the same patient on the same day will only be counted once to try and remove duplicated records.

Discharges

All discharges recorded for this programme are presented below by year and month. Patients who were re-admitted then discharged a second time will be counted twice.

Discharge status

Discharge status is presented by quarter and year. Data for this table is taken from the registration form. Where a patient has been allocated an exit date but no exit status has been recorded, they are counted in the relevent quarter but categorised as Missing.
